1 (c) “Photo identification card” means a document which
2 includes the name, date of birth and a color picture of the offender.
3 (d) “Promising practice reentry program” means a reentry
4 program that has strong quantitative and qualitative data showing
5 positive outcomes, but does not have sufficient research or
6 replication to support recognition as an evidence-based practice.
7 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
